After a 12-week trial that ended with jurors saying they did not believe two Hollywood stuntmen central to the prosecution's case, actor Robert Blake was found not guilty Wednesday of fatally shooting his wife.
Blake, 71, is accused of killing his wife, Bonny Lee Bakley, 44, who was shot in his car near Vitello's, his favorite restaurant.
In the absence of direct evidence, jurors were asked to believe testimony from the stuntmen who testified that Blake had asked them to kill Bakley two months before her murder.
